{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"author":"Miguel de Guzman","homeCity":"Bulacan, Philippines"}},"markdownRemark":{"html":"</br>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/32325e5a864932fc2d3ccf5a51aa0e1d/a1d65/genghizkhan.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 49.89473684210526%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"genghizkhan\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/32325e5a864932fc2d3ccf5a51aa0e1d/f8fb9/genghizkhan.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/32325e5a864932fc2d3ccf5a51aa0e1d/e8976/genghizkhan.jpg 148w,\n/static/32325e5a864932fc2d3ccf5a51aa0e1d/63df2/genghizkhan.jpg 295w,\n/static/32325e5a864932fc2d3ccf5a51aa0e1d/f8fb9/genghizkhan.jpg 590w,\n/static/32325e5a864932fc2d3ccf5a51aa0e1d/85e3d/genghizkhan.jpg 885w,\n/static/32325e5a864932fc2d3ccf5a51aa0e1d/a1d65/genghizkhan.jpg 950w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>War is one of the greatest and worst tools ever wielded by humanity. Everyone in this world have been forged over 3.6 million years of war starting from our primal ancestors trying to stay alive to warlords carving their swords and spears to become momentary Gods of multiple lands. Let’s start this series with one of my favorite historical figures: Genghis Khan.</p>\n<p>Genghis Khan is one of the few of us who have changed the path of history - using war as a tool to implement his own aspirations for the world to follow. His influence in history is immense, to name such:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Co-existence of different cultures and religions</li>\n<li>Silk Road</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Genghis_Khan\">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Genghis_Khan</a></p>","excerpt":"War is one of the greatest and worst tools ever wielded by humanity. Everyone in this world have been forged over 3.6 million years of war…","fields":{"tagSlugs":["/tags/talking-history/","/tags/creating-art/","/tags/blog/"]},"frontmatter":{"title":"Lessons of War - Genghis Khan","tags":["talking-history","creating-art","blog"],"date":"March 20, 2019"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/lessons-of-war-genghiz-khan/"}}